WEBVTT

01:15.426 --> 01:17.008
How are you this morning?

01:18.250 --> 01:19.332
You guys are awake.

01:19.372 --> 01:20.894
You must have had some rest this week, have you?

01:22.016 --> 01:23.038
No, y'all after that one.

01:23.599 --> 01:29.227
I got you turning your Bibles if you have them with you to John chapter 8 verse number 31.

01:30.088 --> 01:37.580
While you're turning there, let me say good morning to those who may be joining us online and also to welcome you to family worship today.

01:38.161 --> 01:39.242
Where's all of our kiddos?

01:39.783 --> 01:41.586
If your kiddos are awake, say, oh, yeah.

01:43.394 --> 01:45.257
The adults are more awake than the kids.

01:47.080 --> 01:48.462
I knew we needed Mountain Dew this morning.

01:48.602 --> 01:49.022
All right.

01:49.123 --> 02:02.983
No, we'd never give your kids Mountain Dew without your permission, but we're so thankful for these days, not just because the kids get to come in here and hang out with us, but also because it gives our volunteers a chance to recuperate, to take a break.

02:03.063 --> 02:07.830
If you're a volunteer who serves in any next generation ministry, would you just put your hand up?

02:08.271 --> 02:08.652
Keep them up.

02:08.692 --> 02:10.194
I just want us to look across the room.

02:10.370 --> 02:11.591
and see how many we have here.

02:11.611 --> 02:15.635
Would you guys let us lead each other to know how much we appreciate the ministry that they do?

02:17.978 --> 02:20.180
And I got to confess, I hate the term volunteer.

02:21.121 --> 02:22.222
I really, really hate it.

02:22.242 --> 02:33.833
I wish there was a better term that would encapsulate what it means to be called and equipped to ministry because everyone who serves in ministry has been called and equipped, right?

02:33.853 --> 02:38.578
And so we are so thankful for those volunteers who work each week

02:38.818 --> 02:45.705
to take care of our children, to pour into our kids, to partner with families so that we can make disciples everywhere.

02:46.806 --> 02:52.211
I love Chuck Swindall, and I read a book many years ago called The Grace Awakening.

02:52.912 --> 03:02.361
And in this book, he draws a parallel between our spiritual condition and the conditions in the South following the Civil War.

03:02.421 --> 03:07.346
In the middle of the war, Abraham Lincoln began to see something happening

03:07.650 --> 03:18.621
as the states were in, in battle against each other, that the slaves of the south were beginning to migrate north to come over that line and wanted to join the Union army.

03:20.163 --> 03:31.135
And so September 22, 1862, Abraham Lincoln wrote what we call today an executive order that would free the slaves.

03:32.076 --> 03:34.418
It's called the Emancipation Proclamation.

03:35.010 --> 03:43.002
And in that, in those bordering states, those that had rebelled against the Union, he said those slaves are now free.

03:44.224 --> 03:51.174
And at that point, it freed 3.1 million of 4 million slaves in America.

03:52.095 --> 04:04.754
Now later toward the end of the Civil War, the Senate would vote in 1864 for the 13th Amendment that would later be passed by the House of Representatives before the war ended.

04:05.250 --> 04:20.896
The war ends in April 1865 and by the end of that year, three-fourths of the United States had ratified the 13th amendment to the Constitution, which that last state happened to be ours, Georgia.

04:20.916 --> 04:32.114
But here's the sad tragedy that even though the slaves had been set free, there were many pockets within the South where those slaves who had now been set free did not know they were free.

04:33.250 --> 04:40.737
The taskmasters on those plantations were continuing to whip and to drive and to make those slaves do work.

04:41.478 --> 04:45.522
They had no clue that they had been set free.

04:46.583 --> 04:56.552
And Chuck Swindall draws a parallel between that and Christians who still live under the bondage of the sin of which they've been forgiven and set free.

04:56.572 --> 05:02.738
And he says this, even though our great emancipator Christ the Lord paid the ultimate price

05:03.042 --> 05:10.729
to overthrow slavery once for all, most Christians act as though they're still held in bondage.

05:12.031 --> 05:19.918
In fact, strange as it is, most seem to prefer the security of slavery to the risks of liberty.

05:20.679 --> 05:25.283
And our slave master Satan loves it so.

05:27.425 --> 05:28.346
And it is sad.

05:28.766 --> 05:32.530
I think the saddest state that a Christian can be in

05:32.930 --> 05:39.517
is one who has claimed to know Jesus Christ, but still lives in the bondage of sin.

05:39.577 --> 05:51.869
There's a huge difference that if sin is that direction, and I'm claiming to know Jesus and I'm running to that sin, then someone who has repented and turned away from that sin and is going in opposite direction.

05:52.570 --> 05:54.872
I think we all agree Christian sin, right?

05:54.972 --> 05:55.493
Yes or no.

05:56.574 --> 06:00.818
But for those of us that know Jesus Christ, we have an advocate through Christ,

06:01.090 --> 06:03.353
for our sins to be forgiven, right?

06:03.373 --> 06:14.889
1 John 1 9 says, if we confess our sins, he is faithful, as we saying, and just to forgive us of our sins and cleanse us from unrighteousness.

06:15.690 --> 06:22.900
But far too many Christians still live under the weight of the sin from which they have been set free.

06:22.940 --> 06:30.610
It would be no different that if we as Americans were still living under the laws

06:30.786 --> 06:35.852
of Britain, even though we had declared independence in 1776.

06:37.794 --> 06:44.161
A change in life is necessary if we are going to live as free men.

06:45.443 --> 06:46.724
And it's hard to do, isn't it?

06:47.485 --> 06:50.228
How many of you in this room have a sin problem?

06:50.248 --> 06:50.969
Don't raise your hands.

06:51.149 --> 06:52.571
Don't tell on yourself.

06:52.591 --> 06:53.992
Everybody has a sin problem.

06:54.012 --> 06:55.634
That's why we needed Jesus, right?

06:56.354 --> 06:59.998
There is no way that you and I can set ourselves free from sin.

07:00.038 --> 07:04.762
That's why the truth is true freedom is found only in Jesus Christ.

07:05.503 --> 07:08.486
Because if we have a sin problem, we have a death problem, right?

07:09.146 --> 07:13.731
But Jesus Christ died on the cross so that our sin that could be paid, right?

07:14.432 --> 07:15.693
But it didn't stop there.

07:16.273 --> 07:17.374
Where's my kids in the house?

07:18.135 --> 07:19.777
What happened to Jesus on Easter?

07:19.877 --> 07:20.097
What?

07:21.418 --> 07:22.640
What happened to Jesus on Easter?

07:24.722 --> 07:25.202
I heard it.

07:25.762 --> 07:32.912
He was raised from the dead by the power of the Holy Spirit proving that death no longer was an issue.

07:33.853 --> 07:40.383
Why do you think the disciples continued in the ministry of Jesus, even though all of them but one died of martyrs death?

07:41.244 --> 07:44.188
Because they knew Jesus had the power to raise them from the dead.

07:44.849 --> 07:54.162
And for us who had that same power living inside of us, why would we continue walking in the path of sin when we had been set free from it and giving a life

07:54.338 --> 08:00.786
that is far more abundant than anything sin will ever deliver to us.

08:00.806 --> 08:10.137
In fact, there was a slave interviewed in 1864 that Shelby Foote wrote about and he said this, I don't know nothing about Abraham Lincoln.

08:10.177 --> 08:14.341
He replied, sipped that he said is free and he said, I don't know about that either.

08:15.743 --> 08:21.650
Following the emancipation proclamation, being declared free yet still living as a slave.

08:23.970 --> 08:25.112
But you know, there's good news.

08:26.915 --> 08:30.661
Our independence day came when Jesus Christ came up out of that grave.

08:31.502 --> 08:40.316
When Christ was raised from the dead, He proved to all of us that sin had been defeated because Jesus paid our sin debt.

08:41.337 --> 08:51.954
And for those that are sitting in these graves all around this world, there's a day coming when Jesus is going to come back and He's going to raise those people back from the dead.

08:52.194 --> 08:59.102
Those of us who are here when it happens, if we've believed in Jesus, we're going to be called up with them and we'll live forever.

09:00.203 --> 09:01.825
I want to partake in that, don't you?

09:03.166 --> 09:05.028
Because the other route isn't too pretty.

09:05.809 --> 09:10.995
I don't want to be stuck in my sin then, and I don't want to be stuck in my sin now.

09:11.936 --> 09:16.341
Those plantation owners had a saying, keep them ignorant and you'll keep them in the field.

09:16.561 --> 09:20.786
Satan's philosopher, you and me, is keep them ignorant and you'll keep them impotent.

09:22.018 --> 09:28.747
If he can keep us stuck in our sin, then we're not gonna tell people about the light of the gospel, are we?

09:29.168 --> 09:30.630
Because we're not living in that light.

09:31.811 --> 09:37.959
And so I'd like to ask you to stand with me as we read through this paragraph found in John eight, starting with verse number 31.

09:38.780 --> 09:48.273
It says this, so Jesus was saying to those Jews who had believed him, if you continue in my word, then you are truly disciples of mine.

09:48.293 --> 09:50.937
I love that phrase, truly disciples.

09:50.977 --> 09:51.858
So there is,

09:52.098 --> 09:58.025
A difference and you will know the truth and the truth will make you free.

09:58.326 --> 10:05.354
That is not some nugget that a lawyer finds and brings into the court to get someone off the hook.

10:05.374 --> 10:09.880
There's a whole different concept in this chapter about the truth.

10:10.881 --> 10:12.343
He goes on to say they answered him.

10:12.924 --> 10:16.969
We are Abraham's descendants and have never been enslaved to anyone.

10:18.030 --> 10:18.411
Good joke.

10:18.771 --> 10:21.234
And how is that you say you will become free?

10:22.210 --> 10:29.480
Jesus answered them, truly, truly, I say to you, everyone who commits sin is the slave of sin.

10:30.141 --> 10:34.767
Whether you've done one, 10 or 10 million, you are a slave of sin.

10:35.368 --> 10:40.895
The slave does not remain in the house forever because he's a slave, but who does?

10:41.236 --> 10:43.398
The son remains forever.

10:44.700 --> 10:52.050
So if the son makes you free, not that truth, if the son makes you free, you,

10:52.194 --> 10:53.896
are free indeed.

10:54.517 --> 10:55.158
Did y'all hear that?

10:55.779 --> 11:00.505
If the sun makes you free, you are free indeed, not Independence Day.

11:01.166 --> 11:04.210
If the sun, I'm gonna say it till we get it.

11:04.230 --> 11:08.736
If the sun has set you free, you are free indeed.

11:08.816 --> 11:09.597
You didn't do it.

11:09.617 --> 11:10.718
I didn't do it.

11:10.939 --> 11:12.120
The government didn't do it.

11:12.481 --> 11:14.023
Jesus Christ did it.

11:14.043 --> 11:19.730
I know that you are Abraham's descendants and he's probably thinking in his mind, you've told me a million times.

11:20.834 --> 11:22.236
Yet you seek to kill me.

11:22.556 --> 11:22.816
Why?

11:23.257 --> 11:26.681
Because my word has no place in you.

11:26.741 --> 11:29.044
Then he makes a contrast.

11:29.224 --> 11:37.455
I speak the things which I have seen with my father, therefore also you do the things which you have heard from your father.

11:37.475 --> 11:40.719
And if you read on down through there, basically you're going to call them the sons of the devil.

11:41.740 --> 11:42.000
Why?

11:42.561 --> 11:46.446
Because they have rejected Jesus for who he is and for what he has said.

11:46.726 --> 11:47.187
Let's pray.

11:47.227 --> 11:49.810
Father, as we spend the next few minutes taking

11:50.114 --> 11:58.923
your word and going through it, I pray father that we can gain a greater appreciation for the freedom that we have in Jesus Christ.

11:59.003 --> 12:01.406
And everyone said, Amen.

12:02.427 --> 12:07.512
Now, years ago, I won't do it this morning, but when I was a child, I used to go around and sing at different churches.

12:07.912 --> 12:08.953
And then my voice changed.

12:10.575 --> 12:11.336
And it wasn't pretty.

12:11.957 --> 12:15.941
You've never been more humiliated than when you pull an alfalfa in front of a church.

12:15.961 --> 12:17.202
Do you know what alfalfa is?

12:17.314 --> 12:20.018
When you should go, he really had, and I did that.

12:20.058 --> 12:20.859
I never sang again.

12:21.700 --> 12:24.223
Until I got older and I could control my baritone voice.

12:24.604 --> 12:31.013
But as I was a child and I was singing, I used to sing a song by Dottie Rambo called, Remind Me Dear Lord.

12:31.053 --> 12:32.915
And the chorus goes something like this.

12:33.376 --> 12:34.457
Roll back the curtains.

12:34.517 --> 12:35.739
I scared you, didn't I?

12:35.759 --> 12:36.600
You thought I was going to sing.

12:37.001 --> 12:39.204
Roll back the curtains of memories now and then.

12:39.264 --> 12:42.428
Show me where you brought me from and where I could have been.

12:42.468 --> 12:46.834
Remember I'm human and humans forget.

12:47.010 --> 12:49.233
So remind me, remind me, dear Lord.

12:49.633 --> 12:55.500
And the tragedy sometimes in Christianity is we get so far removed after we've been saved that we get over being saved.

12:55.560 --> 13:04.611
We forget that the whole reason that we came to know Jesus Christ in the first place was because we were poor, destitute and dead in our trespasses.

13:04.952 --> 13:13.682
And we forget that our freedom, when we experience freedom, it begins with realizing the gravity of bondage.

13:14.658 --> 13:17.261
When I ask kids, what's the worst thing that you've ever done?

13:17.281 --> 13:20.485
A few weeks ago, a little girl told me, well, I've never done anything wrong.

13:23.188 --> 13:26.252
So I say, well, let me ask you, what's the worst thing you could do?

13:26.292 --> 13:28.855
And sometimes in their innocence, they can't answer that question.

13:29.336 --> 13:31.018
But adults, let me ask you the question.

13:31.539 --> 13:35.103
As a sinner, what is the worst thing that you could do?

13:36.204 --> 13:44.114
You may not have ever done it, but Jesus even confronts that in Matthew chapter five when he says, if you looked on a woman and lusted after her, you've committed

13:44.226 --> 13:44.867
adultery.

13:45.127 --> 13:48.051
If you've hated your brother, it's as if you have killed him.

13:49.112 --> 14:01.828
And so for you and me to stand here today in our freedom, we forget that there was a great, great chasm that we found ourselves in when Jesus saved us from our sin.

14:02.629 --> 14:07.855
And so he begins to talk to these Jews that the Bible said had believed.

14:07.875 --> 14:13.522
Well, we don't really know what they believed, but this belief they had was not a belief until salvation.

14:14.562 --> 14:26.738
So Jesus was saying to the Jews who had believed, if you continue in my word, if you continue in my word, why would they believe Jesus and not take what he said at heart?

14:26.778 --> 14:28.861
Well, I believe there was two things going on.

14:29.582 --> 14:34.369
Number one, Jesus was trying to convey to them God sent him.

14:34.429 --> 14:44.402
The father had sent him, and in previous chapters we read that when he called God my father, he was making himself equal

14:44.738 --> 14:45.679
and God.

14:45.719 --> 14:50.847
He was God in the flesh and they could not accept that.

14:51.608 --> 14:58.718
Because if they accepted Him as true, then they had to accept what He said as true.

14:59.399 --> 15:03.385
You know, over the years I've talked to different people about how they know if they're saved or not saved.

15:03.405 --> 15:04.266
You know where I've landed?

15:05.528 --> 15:07.250
What does Jesus say?

15:07.311 --> 15:12.498
Because I can't base it on my experience, though I have one,

15:12.802 --> 15:15.105
Because your experience and my experience is going to be different.

15:15.446 --> 15:19.672
The only thing that's consistent is what Jesus says.

15:20.714 --> 15:28.386
And he said to that same group, if you do not receive me, you will die in your sins.

15:29.227 --> 15:39.983
So I ask us this question, do we know that Jesus is the, the only begotten son of God?

15:40.304 --> 15:41.906
He's not a great teacher.

15:42.082 --> 15:43.604
He's not a good model.

15:44.064 --> 15:48.610
He is God in the flesh who has come to reveal God's will.

15:48.730 --> 15:55.739
And the point he makes in this whole paragraph is that if you are children of Abraham, you would be celebrating me being here too.

15:56.079 --> 15:58.202
But as it is, you're doing exactly the opposite.

15:58.503 --> 16:04.610
You want to kill me because if I kill the messenger, I kill the message, right?

16:05.852 --> 16:07.854
They answered him, we were Abraham's descendants.

16:09.016 --> 16:10.898
Our salvation is not

16:11.074 --> 16:17.481
secured in how many bibles I have, how many generations my family has been in a church.

16:18.102 --> 16:24.408
It isn't conditioned upon whether or not I wear Christian paraphernalia or listen to Christian music.

16:24.869 --> 16:34.079
The only thing that secures me is the word of Jesus Christ that he died on the cross, paid for our sins and was raised again.

16:34.780 --> 16:35.801
That's my security.

16:36.742 --> 16:40.626
And so when I counsel young kids, like my son, I'm going to use him as the example.

16:41.282 --> 16:45.528
When he was saved a few years ago, I asked him, son, how do you know that you have been saved?

16:47.131 --> 16:54.082
And he said, because of Jesus, not because of what he did coming down to an altar or praying.

16:54.382 --> 16:56.866
He said, it's because of what Jesus did.

16:59.270 --> 17:00.471
And I think we forget that.

17:00.491 --> 17:05.840
We forget like these guys where we have never been enslaved to anyone.

17:07.362 --> 17:10.066
They were celebrating the feast of booths.

17:10.562 --> 17:16.370
which was a celebration in the fall when they would commemorate the wilderness wandering.

17:17.412 --> 17:23.681
And so they were celebrating that they had been rescued from Egypt as what slaves.

17:24.902 --> 17:26.585
And so they're going all the way back to Abraham.

17:26.605 --> 17:33.074
It's like my identity is wrapped up that I'm a child of Abraham, but they forgot that children of Abraham eventually ended up in Egypt.

17:33.154 --> 17:35.678
as slaves, and God made a way for them to get out.

17:35.978 --> 17:44.910
They forgot that after Rehoboam became king and the kingdom split that the northern kingdom in 722 BC was taken over by the Assyrians.

17:45.992 --> 17:56.146
And then the remnants of Judah and Benjamin were taken into deportation over a period of years from 605 to 586 BC into Babylon.

17:56.738 --> 18:01.225
And then they, some of them returned and they were still under the Greeks and now they were under the Romans.

18:01.545 --> 18:04.650
And he's looking at them going, you've never been enslaved to anyone?

18:07.675 --> 18:09.237
Are you making your own choices?

18:10.459 --> 18:12.202
Are you living out your life in freedom?

18:13.264 --> 18:19.433
And they had to answer the question, no, because their people had been enslaved for a long time.

18:19.894 --> 18:22.418
But he's talking about the spiritual side.

18:22.498 --> 18:24.721
They were dead in their trespasses.

18:24.981 --> 18:31.249
They knew what the Old Testament said, but Old Testament revelation is standing in front of them and they couldn't accept Jesus.

18:32.631 --> 18:35.695
They could not understand the gravity of their sin.

18:36.156 --> 18:40.221
In fact, he was challenging them to think about being an authentic disciple.

18:40.702 --> 18:43.165
And this is what I define as an authentic disciple of Christ.

18:43.606 --> 18:50.034
It's someone who abides, which means to live and remains in Jesus and in

18:50.146 --> 18:50.807
His Word.

18:50.867 --> 18:51.788
Where did I come up with that?

18:51.828 --> 18:53.109
Well, I'm glad you asked.

18:53.129 --> 18:55.091
John 15, 7, 3, 8 says this.

18:55.592 --> 19:01.638
If you abide in me and my words abide in you, ask whatever you wish, it'll be done for you.

19:01.658 --> 19:03.681
So I want a new Lego set.

19:04.862 --> 19:05.703
Would y'all pray with me?

19:06.644 --> 19:06.884
No.

19:08.105 --> 19:09.907
My Father is glorified by this.

19:09.927 --> 19:11.949
So it's not us asking for stuff.

19:13.031 --> 19:19.858
We're asking that God will do a work through us that we might be the light of the gospel to the world.

19:20.578 --> 19:28.185
But look what he says, that you bear much fruit, so prove to be my disciples.

19:29.807 --> 19:38.295
You see, when I'm stuck in sin, when I still have one foot stuck in the life that I used to live, I'm impotent.

19:38.315 --> 19:39.256
I'm held down.

19:39.837 --> 19:40.838
I'm in bondage.

19:41.338 --> 19:49.426
And just like the pockets in the south where the plantation owners were still whipping their slaves and making them do what they want to do, Satan is doing the same thing.

19:49.506 --> 19:53.932
to you and me when we ignore the gravity that sin presents.

19:54.753 --> 19:56.395
It's all around us.

19:56.795 --> 19:59.358
You know how I know sin is around us because I smell death.

19:59.939 --> 20:01.421
I smell suffering.

20:01.441 --> 20:02.202
I see evil.

20:02.662 --> 20:03.243
What about you?

20:03.403 --> 20:06.607
Do you see the same things or am I just kind of imagining that?

20:07.468 --> 20:10.192
When I turn on the TV, I see a lot of destruction.

20:10.432 --> 20:11.594
How many of you remember Neil Bortz?

20:13.516 --> 20:14.237
A few of you do.

20:14.357 --> 20:14.838
All right.

20:15.639 --> 20:18.322
Neil Bortz was on WSB for many, many years.

20:18.754 --> 20:20.477
And he gets on Twitter a lot.

20:21.258 --> 20:25.504
And about every other day he will, he will put on there, look at the culture of violence.

20:25.524 --> 20:30.432
Every other day he says, one time in tweet, I wake up seeing who's dead again in Atlanta.

20:31.493 --> 20:33.537
It's all around us.

20:34.378 --> 20:37.763
We know sin because of the repercussions of sin.

20:38.584 --> 20:39.606
And I don't want to live in that.

20:40.928 --> 20:45.735
I want to live in the freedom that Christ has brought to me into you.

20:46.296 --> 20:47.538
He told that same group,

20:47.650 --> 20:48.671
You are from below.

20:48.711 --> 20:51.034
I am from above.

20:51.075 --> 20:52.116
That's what they couldn't handle.

20:52.737 --> 20:54.319
He kept saying, I came from the father.

20:54.359 --> 20:57.563
I came down from above, which meant he was saying, I am God.

20:57.944 --> 21:02.930
And of course they were offended by this, but you are of this world and I am not of this world.

21:02.950 --> 21:09.779
Therefore I said to you that you will die in your sin for unless you believe that I am he, you will die in your sins.

21:11.301 --> 21:13.043
How grave is our sin?

21:14.365 --> 21:15.026
It's death.

21:16.962 --> 21:23.630
And for us today, if we want to experience that freedom, we can't be like an Indian monkey.

21:25.011 --> 21:27.034
I saw a monkey on my vacation a few weeks ago.

21:27.394 --> 21:31.759
No, I'm not talking about my kids, but we went rafting down the Silver River.

21:32.080 --> 21:39.769
Silver Springs went kayak and it was so cool, but there was a monkey down drinking at the water's edge and they warned us, don't mess with it.

21:39.789 --> 21:44.114
So we didn't, but it was just freaky to see a monkey in the wilderness.

21:44.578 --> 21:55.895
But in India, supposedly when they wanted to catch a monkey, they would take a coconut and hollow it out and put a hole in it, just big enough for a monkey to reach his hand inside of it.

21:55.915 --> 21:59.401
And they would put rice or something inside of the coconut.

21:59.421 --> 22:08.575
